I sincerely thank the founder, Sister Asayech, and all working in the center for this loving care and support they are providing to more that 280 children and thier mothers currently and also thank all who are supporting this noble work.

For the last 16 years the center has been providing wholistic support for children with multiple special needs and disabilities including education, medical care, feeding and most importantly supports thier mothers.

Signs and symptoms of active TB include:
* Coughing for three or more weeks
* Coughing up blood or mucus
* Chest pain, or pain with breathing or coughing
* Unintentional weight loss
* Fatigue
* Fever
* Night sweats
* Chills
* Loss of appetite

With the heightened concern of #COVID19, simple but effective measures to be safer:
- Frequent hand washing with soap 
- Avoid shaking hands 
- Don't touch your face
- If you have symptoms like fever, cough, sneezing; wear masks 
- Sneeze or cough on flexed elbow
